article.description: — Colbey Ross had 25 points and 12 assists as Pepperdine topped Santa Clara 78-70 in the West Coast Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Saturday night.
article.headline: Ross leads Pepperdine over Santa Clara 78-70 in WCC tourney
article.linkText: Ross leads Pepperdine over Santa Clara 78-70 in WCC tourney
article.story: PARADISE, Nev. -- — Colbey Ross had 25 points and 12 assists as Pepperdine topped Santa Clara 78-70 in the West Coast Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Saturday night. Kessler Edwards added 21 points for the Waves. Pepperdine plays No. 2 seed BYU in Monday's semifinals. Ross converted all 12 of his free throw attempts. Edwards also had 11 rebounds. Jan Zidek had 13 points and 10 rebounds for Pepperdine (12-11). Jade’ Smith added 11 points. Guglielmo Caruso had 16 points and nine rebounds for the Broncos (12-8). Josip Vrankic added 15 points and 10 rebounds. Jalen Williams had 13 points and 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
